COMPILING and INSTALLING:

If you got a official release tar archive do:
    ./configure
    
( otherwise if you got this from enlightenment cvs do: ./autogen.sh )
    
Then to compile:
    make

To install (run this as root, or the user who handles installs):
    make install

The modules will be installed to e17's modules_extra dir, probably
<prefix>/lib/enlightenment/modules_extra/<modulename>/<arch>/module.so

To load the module issue "enlightenment_remote -module-load <modulename>".

